Tinsel actor Ibrahim Suleiman has announced his newest investment as a co-founder with co-founder Chidinma Igbokweuche. Suleiman and his partner announced the launch of their new brand called Nollydata. According to the actor, Nollydata can be described as Nollywood’s first-ever database website. The pair unveiled the website via their individual on Monday, February 7, 2022.   Asa joins Spotify EQUAL Music Programme as ambassador of the…     Laolu Gbenjo set for U.S. Tour     13 things you probably didn’t know about Oxlade   Sulamain also noted that the initiative would make the process of filmmaking a lot easier for practitioners in Nollywood. - Advertisement - “A database platform for talent and crew to be able to showcase their work to the world and the entire industry. Today, we’re proud to announce the launch of Nollydata, Nollywood’s first-ever database website,” Sulaiman disclosed. Continuing, he said, “Nollydata is a one-stop website for all things Nollywood, a community for filmmakers to display their projects, talents, and creativity to the world. Our mission is to create a space that makes it easier to find information on all things Nollywood. “From your old Nigerian movies to your favourites features, we want to help filmmakers find talent and crew for their next project with ease. To say we’re proud to finally present this to the world is an understatement.”